      <scopecontent id="aspace_bd585e78f8f6f66b031fa467e2e8f228">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of a scrapbook for the years 1893-1897 kept by Caroline Suydam Duer McLanahan. Included are invitations, calling cards, programs and other memorabilia relating to New Haven and New York social life and to social events at Yale University. Her husband, George X. McLanahan, was a member of the Yale College Class of 1896.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
